verses.roman:
advaita-ācārya--īśvarera aṁśa-varya
tāṅra tattva-nāma-guṇa, sakali āścarya

synonyms: advaita-ācārya—Advaita Ācārya Prabhu; īśvarera—of the Supreme Lord; aṁśa-varya—principal part; tāṅra—His; tattva—truths; nāma—names; guṇa—attributes; sakali—all; āścarya—wonderful.
translation: Śrī Advaita Ācārya is the principal limb of the Supreme Lord. His truths, names and attributes are all wonderful.
